text.tspan: Total factor productivity (TFP) is an estimate of how efficiently an economy turns its inputs into outputs. It is
defined as the part of GDP not explained by capital or labor input. This data is adjusted for inflation and
differences in living costs between countries. TFP is measured relative to each country's TFP in 2021.
Data source: Feenstra et al. - Penn World Table (2025)
